<TEXT>
a civil air patrol plane 
crashed into the gulf of mexico during a training flight sunday 
afternoon killing the pilot and three teenage cadets authorities 
said 
the singleengine cessna 182 was reported down shortly before 
200 pm three miles off the southernmost point of st petersburg 
beach which is across boca ciega bay from st petersburg 
we sent a cutter and a helicopter out to the scene and all 
they found was debris on the surface of the water said lt david 
vaughn of the coast guards st petersburg station divers later 
found the wreckage in about 25 feet of water with the bodies of 
four people inside 
the plane had taken off from a small st petersburg airport the 
cause of the crash was not known 
a second small plane crash sunday near mound city kan killed 
a st joseph mo couple and their 16yearold granddaughter 
authorities said 
the singleengine mooney crashed into a field 5 miles north of 
mound city at about 1 pm said jim grayson a dispatcher for the 
kansas highway patrol 
the victims were identified as james w worley 66 who was the 
pilot his wife josephine g worley 57 and their granddaughter 
angela j procella 16 of kirbyville texas 
in the florida crash a 46yearold pilot was at the controls 
and three cadets aged 14 to 18 came along on the training flight 
said cmdr frank sportell of the civil air patrols pinellas county 
squadron 
this was what is known as a civil air patrol cadet 
orientation sportell these young people werent familiar with 
flying and this was just to give them a chance to get up in the air 
with a senior pilot they were not flying the plane 
the civilian organization which helps search for downed 
aircraft often enlists young people interested in aviation careers 
the dead were identified as pilot wayne mcnight shawn kelley 
18 joseph flythe 17 and damion weber 14 all of the st 
petersburg area the coast guard said 
