<TEXT>
the rolling stones launched their 1989 
tour saturday night when they pulled into a tiny new haven nighclub 
for a tuneup that thrilled 700 fans who paid 3 apiece for the 
impromptu gig 
welcome to new haven mick jagger shouted as the band took 
the stage at toads place this is our debut show of the 1989 
tour 
the stones who have been rehearsing for the last six weeks in 
the tiny northwest connecticut town of washington brought the 
house down with an 11song hourlong set 
the tour is the stones first in eight years 
the band opened the set with start me up and played several 
songs from their new album steel wheels which is to be 
released aug 29 
the show featured the classic songs that have made the stones 
one of rocks most enduring bands including jumpin jack 
flash honky tonk woman brown sugar and its only 
rock n roll 
jagger who wore a tshirt promoting the 1989 north american 
tour underneath a blue shirt traded licks on the guitar on several 
songs with stones guitarists keith richard and ron wood 
the stones have traditionally tried to opened new tours with 
impromptu shows at small venues 
word that the stones were going to play at toads leaked out 
over the last several days said storm norman music director at 
webefm in westport fans lined up outside the club and hundreds 
were turned away before the stones took the stage at 1045 pm 
saturday 
the audience included a number of washington conn residents 
who worked for the stones during their stay at a former girls 
boarding school in washington 
jennifer almquist 39 who runs an art gallery in washington 
worked for the last six weeks as jaggers housekeeper almquist 
who attended her first rolling stones concert in newark nj in 
1964 said she enjoyed her job 
i just spent the last 30 days being his housekeeper and it 
changed my life almquist said 
also in the audience was singersongwriter daryl hall 
