space shuttle columbia 
swooped out of orbit and landed safely in the mojave desert on 
sunday at the end of a secret mission in which the astronauts 
released a superspy satellite to photograph military targets around 
the globe 
air force col brewster shaw commander of the fiveman crew 
guided the 97ton winged spaceship to a touchdown on a hard clay 
runway at 637 am pdt after a flight that covered more than 2 
million miles in five days one hour 
a super team and a great machine welcome home columbia 
frank culbertson an astronaut who served as the spacecraft 
communicator at mission control in houston told the crew as the 
spacecraft rolled down the runway after a perfect landing 
after securing systems aboard the spacecraft for nearly an hour 
the astronauts left the vehicle and did a walkaround inspection 
they found a few of the 30000 heat protection tiles missing a 
normal condition 
then they were driven to a nearby facility for physical exams 
and showers 
an hour before landing shaw fired twin braking rockets to drop 
the shuttle out of orbit and start it on a fiery dive through the 
atmosphere and into this desert air base 80 miles north of los 
angeles 
