<TEXT>
rep mickey leland never freed of his torment 
over a dying girl in ethiopia years ago was drawn again and again 
to the place he called the end of the earth 
george thomas mickey leland a sixterm houston democrat and 
chairman of the house select committee on hunger was on his fifth 
visit to refugee camps near the sudan border when the plane 
carrying his party crashed 
the wreckage was found sunday six days after the plane vanished 
after taking off in bad weather from addis ababa the ethiopian 
capital and heading for the fugnido refugee camp 480 miles 
southwest 
although there were no immediate positive identifications of the 
bodies found by paramedics dropped from a helicopter rescuers said 
no one could have survived the fiery crash 
president bush quickly expressed condolences to the 44yearold 
congressmans wife as well as to the families and friends of those 
who died with him on what the president called a noble 
cause 
it was in 1985 when leland recalled standing in a refugee camp 
10 months earlier and asking a relief official about a little girl 
who looked to be about 70 or 80 years old a skeleton of a 
person with a thin layer of brown skin draped on her who had just 
a faint breath of life in her 
while i was talking to him she died i can see her face right 
now every day i see her face leland said at the time 
twice chairman of the congressional black caucus leland 
evolved by his own account from a firebrand black activist 
to an activist on behalf of humanity everywhere whether it is in 
ethiopia south africa chile in any part of the world where 
people are desperate and hungry for the freedoms and rights they 
deserve as human beings 
his deeds reflected the breadth of that concern just as he 
pressed for famine relief in africa he fought as relentlessly to 
feed the homeless in the united states he went to vietnam to 
retrieve three children for their families in america last 
october he went to cuba where he helped negotiate the release of 
three political prisoners and their families 
in a bid to bridge festering hostility between black and jewish 
communities he supervised for 10 years a program under which poor 
black kids from houston were sent to israel for six weeks to learn 
about the jewish culture and heritage 
a roman catholic leland once bicycled through israel and often 
cited the talmud the jewish commentary on the old testament if 
you save one life you save the whole world was his favorite 
passage 
hes someone who cared and made a difference a militant 
man who found he could change the system more from the inside than 
the outside said rep gary l ackerman dny who served with 
leland on the hunger committee and thrice joined him on trips to 
ethiopia 
after offering that assessment of his friend ackerman went to 
ethiopia to join the search he was aboard the air force helicopter 
that found the wreckage 
when leland moved from the texas legislature to congress in 
1979 replacing the retired rep barbara jordan he almost 
immediately began pushing for a special committee on world hunger 
even after he recited the horrors he witnessed in a 1983 trip to 
ethiopia he was opposed by people who argued yet another select 
committee was a waste of money and by those who viewed it as an 
infringement of their own turf foreign relations agriculture and 
appropriations 
leland wouldnt back off instead he rallied all the volunteer 
organizations concerned with hunger and enlisted the help of 
celebrities like valerie harper john denver and cliff robertson 
house speaker thomas p oneill jr dmass lent his prestige 
leland invited members of the established committees to join his 
unofficial caucus on hunger finally in the spring of 1984 he got 
his committee and the momentum that resulted in 800 million for 
famine relief the following fiscal year he personally convinced 
president reagan to divert a ship loaded with food to ethiopia 
as a member of the energy and commerce subcommittee on 
telecommunications he repeatedly tangled with the television 
networks over black representation on and off camera in their 
shows a year before diahann carrol and billy dee williams appeared 
on dynasty he needled abc executives about why the show didnt 
have any black characters 
leland said he learned his values from his mother a teacher who 
had put herself through school working as a shortorder cook as a 
pharmacy student at texas southern university he joined a 
volunteer group which operated free health clinics he was drawn 
too to the black panther party which also operated free clinics 
and gave breakfasts to needy black children 
his political influences ranged from stokely carmichael to 
malcolm x to tanzanian president julius nyerere and he eventually 
formed his own black community action team known as the black 
cats and helped establish three health clinics in houston texas 
conservatives assailed him a radical an image not helped during 
his days in the state legislature by his seveninch afro a leather 
shoulder bag and his dashikis long since replaced by threepiece 
business suits 
i never considered myself to be a radical because i fought for 
the rights of human beings he said in 1972 in his first race 
for public office he was elected to the texas house where he 
championed health issues included a genericdrug law over the 
stiff lobbying of the pharmaceutical lobby 
when he ran for congress in 1978 he had no republican 
opposition and defeated a socialist workers party candidate with 
more than 96 percent of the vote he won reelection five times 
with similar ease despite a 1988 primary challenge from elizabeth 
spates who charged that leland had lost touch with constituents 
while seeking national exposure as spokesman for the hungry and 
homeless 
theres people ive not touched in a long time he 
acknowledged i have been on the road quite a bit 
but he earned respect even from staunch conservatives like 
illinois rep henry j hyde the ranking republican on the house 
select committee on intelligence who recently wrote in the houston 
chronicle that lelands personal diplomacy with ethiopian and 
sudanese officials opened up lifesustaining corridors in the 
border region between the two countries a peaceful relief 
supply route 
leland who also served on the committee on post office and 
civil service often thrust himself into the position of mediator 
in matters of international or interracial consequence 
he was closer to cuban president fidel castro than any other 
member of congress while i disagree with his fundamental 
ideology i respect him for his intellect leland said castro 
returned that sentiment and leland was often tapped to open 
avenues of communication between the united states and cuba 
in april the union of american hebrew congregations paid 
special tribute to his work in uniting blacks and jews 
in the 1984 democratic presidential primary leland supported 
former vice president walter mondale over the rev jesse jackson 
angering many of his black colleagues in the process 
but jackson chose leland as one of the top four fundraisers in 
his 1988 presidential campaign and praised the consistent streak 
of humanity in mickey leland during an election year trip to 
houston 
leland often had been mentioned as a possible mayoral candidate 
in houston despite his political roots he maintained a close 
relationship with the citys business establishment and he and his 
wife alison and their son jarret shared a fashionable home in 
an upscale neighborhood 
the americans for democratic action called him a liberal 
hero early this year and leland relished the label despite the 
bashing that many fellow democrats took over the l word in last 
years presidential campaign 
some of use are not afraid to be called liberal and 
progressive and to continue to fight for our place in the sun 
he said eventually well get there 
