cigarette smoke led mirchandani to the possibility that the same 
was true of the passive inhalation of crack smoke he said even 
though the mother said she didnt smoke around the baby the 
childs room was not wellventilated and other adults addicted to 
the drug smoked it in the house 
similar cases in philadelphia and new york city supported the 
doctors theory he said 
cocaine can be toxic at any dose and is proven to be 
dangerous and deadly in even small doses even in adults he 
said i would expect a much heightened toxicity for infants its 
common sense something that is toxic for adults would be even 
more toxic for an infant 
