<TEXT>
for more than a year platoon leader falk turba 
patrolled the border between east and west germany his automatic 
rifle at the ready to stop anyone attempting to flee to the west 
in july he slipped away from his comrades tossed his rifle 
aside and scrambled over the barbedwire and concrete barriers to 
west germany 
i just couldnt take it anymore turba said in an interview 
in west berlin on sunday the 28th anniversary of the building of 
the berlin wall 
turba 20 spoke of the daily life of communist east germanys 
elite border troopers young men selected by communist party and 
military officials because of their loyality to the state 
turba who grew up in dresden said border guards were told in 
april that a shoottokill order against civilians trying to flee 
east germany had been lifted 
but he said most of his comrades had quietly ignored the order 
during their border service 
only about 10 percent of the hardcore gungho troops would 
shoot at an unarmed civilian attempting to flee turba said 
theyre the macho types who like strutting around with their 
machine guns looking tough 
but he said it was a great risk for the border guards to allow 
someone to escape 
if you let someone escape you go to prison he said its 
also very risky because you patrol in pairs and you never know 
what the other guy is thinking or what he would do 
but i hoped and many others did as well that i would never 
have to arrest someone 
he said electronic listening devices and alarm systems attack 
dogs and rows of barbedwire usually slowed wouldbe escapees long 
enough that border troops could arrest them 
many of those caught were given long prison terms 
according to west german statistics 191 people have been killed 
trying to escape since the berlin wall was erected in 1961 and the 
border between the two germanies was sealed by barriers 
but about 218000 people managed to escape including 2614 
border troops according to the statistics 
turba said he decided to flee because he had little hope of 
political and economic changes in his country 
unlike hungary and poland where reform communists have 
