water for about seven hours when it was called off at 330 pm 
a passing boater and the erie county sheriffs marine patrol 
helped the swimmers and the people in the boat that sank schaus 
said he said the marine patrol gave him a ticket for having an 
unregistered rowboat the boat that didnt sink 
schaus said he didnt know why the other boat sank but 
speculated that a large wave or a loose drainage plug may have been 
the cause 
schaus has made the swim twice before for other charities but 
sunday was the first time he did it handcuffed which he said was a 
metaphor for the loss of freedom in china to swim he used a 
modified dog paddle 
xianglong zhang one of the students at the state university of 
new york at buffalo who swam with schaus said he was more 
disappointed for schaus than in his own failure to finish the swim 
